======================================================================
PART 1: THE NUMBER 960
======================================================================
960 = {2: 6, 3: 1, 5: 1}
960 = 2^6 * 3 * 5 = 64 * 15
960 = 8! / (7 * 6) = 40320 / 42
960 / 6 = 160 = 2^5 * 5
960 / 120 = 8
960 / 360 = 2.6666666666666665
960 / 720 = 1.3333333333333333

120960 / 960 = 126 = stabilizer of a partition
  126 = 2 * 63 = 2 * 7 * 9
  OR: 126 = C(9,4) = 9!/(4!5!)

Stabilizer of a Baer partition: 126
  126 = 2 * 3^2 * 7
  126 / 2 = 63 = 7 * 9 = |PGL(2,F_4)| / ... no
  |PGL(2,F_8)| = (8^3-8)/(8-1) = 504/7 = 72
  Actually: |PSL(2,F_7)| = 168, |PSL(2,F_8)| = 504
  126 = 168 * 3/4 = not clean
  126 = 2 * 63 = 2 * 63
  63 = 2^6 - 1 (Mersenne)

960 as group-theoretic object:
  960 = |Sp(4,F_2)| = |Omega(5,F_2)|? No, |Sp(4,2)| = 720
  960 = 2 * |S_5 x Z_2| = 2 * 240? No
  Actually: 960 = 2^6 * 15 = 64 * 15

960 = 8 * 120 = 8 * |S_5| = 8 * |Aut(Petersen)|
  Each Baer subplane is in 8 partitions
  |Aut(Petersen)| = |S_5| = 120

======================================================================
PART 2: STRUCTURE OF BAER DISJOINTNESS
======================================================================
Baer disjointness graph:
  360 vertices, each with degree 16
  Total edges: 360 * 16 / 2 = 2880
  Edge density: 0.0446
  Triangles: 960 (= partitions)
  360 * 8 / 3 = 960 ✓

  Each edge in exactly 1 triangle!
  → Each pair of disjoint Baer subplanes has a UNIQUE
    complement that is also a Baer subplane.
  → The 960 partitions are a STEINER-LIKE system:
    each disjoint pair extends uniquely to a partition!

  The 16 disjoint neighbors of each B decompose into
  8 matched pairs (from the 8 partitions containing B)
  → The disjoint neighborhood = 8K_2 (8 disjoint edges)
  → Lambda = 1 (adjacent pair shares exactly 1 common neighbor)
  → This is related to the cocktail party CP(8)!

======================================================================
PART 3: THE HESSE CONFIGURATION AND PARTITION STRUCTURE
======================================================================
Partition stabilizer order: 126
  If S_3 action on {B1,B2,B3}: pointwise stab = 126/6 = 21
  If Z_3 action: pointwise stab = 126/3 = 42
  21 = H_forb_2 = |PG(2,F_4)| points = |Aut(Fano)| / 8
  42 = 2 * 21 = |PGL(2,F_7)| / 4

If Z_2 action (Frobenius): pointwise stab = 126/2 = 63
  63 = 7 * 9 = 2^6 - 1 (Mersenne)
  63 = H_forb_1 * 9 = 7 * 9
  H(QR_7) * |Aut(QR_7)| = 189 * 21 = 3969 = 63^2 !!!

  BEAUTIFUL: 63 = sqrt(H(QR_7) * |Aut(QR_7)|)
  The partition stabilizer connects to the QR_7 invariant!

